    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Morning light filters through stained glass windows, casting prismatic colors across towering shelves of ancient tomes. The Whispering Archives stretch before you\u2014a vast circular chamber of knowledge, its brass ladders gleaming as they glide on invisible rails between scrolls and codices. Dust motes dance in the beams like tiny constellations.\n\nYou are Aric, a scholar-warrior who traded the sword for the pen years ago\u2014until the rumors began. Whispers of a lost codex hidden within these archives, a book that contains secrets capable of reshaping the realm. You've spent weeks cataloging the outer rings, but the true treasures lie deeper.\n\nThe head librarian, a perpetually startled-looking elf named Thalindor, watches you from behind his desk. \"Bright and early, I see,\" he calls out. \"The restricted section opens in an hour if you're still intent on... unsupervised exploration.\" His tone suggests he very much hopes you are not.",
      "sequence_id": 4,
      "actor": "gemini"
    },
    {
      "text": "Research Public Stacks - Spend the hour in the public archives looking for any references to the lost codex",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 5
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Morning (09:00:00) in the Whispering Archives\u2014you spend an productive hour among the public stacks, running your fingers along weathered spines and cross-referencing catalog entries. Most volumes are mundane: histories of forgotten kingdoms, agricultural treatises, astronomical observations from centuries past.\n\nBut tucked behind a false panel in a dusty history of the Mage Wars, you discover something intriguing: a marginal note in faded ink. \"The Seventeen Silences\u2014banned by the Conclave of 843, all copies destroyed. See restricted catalog, case 7, row 12.\"\n\nYour heart quickens. The lost codex isn't merely hidden\u2014it's been deliberately erased from history. Someone went to great lengths to bury this knowledge.\n\nAs you copy the reference into your notes, you notice Thalindor watching you more closely now. The elf's ears are twitchy, his fingers drumming against his desk. When your eyes meet, he quickly looks away.\n\nThe restricted section is now open.",
      "actor": "gemini",
      "sequence_id": 6
    },
    {
